Text.Value: *You think of the thousands of souls down waiting in the Underdark. Lost, leaderless...*
*You come to slowly, the events of recent days drifting back in fragments, like a half-remembered dream.*
*And who's to say that if you faced him, you wouldn't still be able to resist? If all this has taught you nothing else, it's that anything is possible.*
*He might wait days or years, but he will come for you. Your reckoning is inevitable.*
*Especially when one of them is the Blade of Avernus. Yes, he'll have to go.*
*Yes, you'd rather like to see what else the world has to offer.*
Who says I'll never walk in the sun again? There may still be a way, if I can find it.
*Even if it's just at night.*
*You'll have to feed, move through the world relying on your wits, and avoid the many people who'll want to kill you. It will be very, very dangerous.*
It's a big world out there. He can't control me if he can't find me.
*There's an almost endless world for you to explore. Even if you can only see it at night.*
*Your life will be nothing but one night of peril after another - a bloody cascade of violence that will leave a trail of bodies everywhere you go.*
*A hero's life won't be an easy one, of course. You'll have to face down every beast, fiend, and lunatic out there, all while dodging assassination attempts, plots, and intrigue.*
*You'll have to see it after dark, of course - when murder, theft, and all manner of lust and debauchery rule the night.*
*And now that Shadowheart has the ear of her god... yes, perhaps it's best if they were removed from the equation.*
*'Yes,' you think to yourself. 'This is going to be fun.'*

Text.Value: *As you run through an ever-growing list of potential enemies, you smile quietly to yourself.*

*If they can destroy the Netherbrain, perhaps they'll think they can destroy the Vampire Ascendant.*
*Perhaps it's best to just lie low for a while. Go out and see the world, maybe?*
Perhaps I'll see what else this world has to offer.
*You consider the fate of their children once they fell into Cazador's grasp...*

Text.Value: *Astarion - Hero of Baldur's Gate. You rather like the sound of that.*

Synopsis: The morning after the climax of the game - Avatar Astarion has defeated the Netherbrain and is now in a room in the Elfsong Tavern, thinking about what comes next.
